Seven women and five men who voted to find Hernandez guilty of murdering Odin Lloyd were sentenced Wednesday to life in prison on Wednesday .
On Thursday, the jury and alternate jurors sat down for a group interview with CNN's Anderson Cooper to talk about the trial that has consumed their lives for the past three months .
Juror Kelly Dorsey, a lifelong Patriots fan, said she locked eyes with Hernandez as the verdict was read .
'He was shaking his head and he mouthed something - and I thought 'You need to look back at the judge'